page.comparison.title: Weapon Comparison Tool
page.datamine.dispersion.info: Dispersion is a hidden mechanic of a gun which determines the cone size where a bullet~s trajectory will be randomly decided.
A lower dispersion means your bullets land closer to where you are aiming.
A high dispersion means you might be aiming directly at someone close to you and still completely miss!
Some exceptions may apply. For example, MG42 has very bad dispersion, but because it fires so fast, you can get a hit even at medium range.
For an easy visualization, see the dispersion simulator in the ~Weapon Tool~ tab
page.datamine.recoil.info: Vertical recoil has strictly a vertical component. It is also constant, there is no randomness to how much the barrel will rise.
However, horizontal recoil has both a vertical and horizontal component. Horizontal recoil actually creates a ring, and the bullet can lang anywhere on that ring.
For an easy visualization, see the recoil simulator in the ~Weapon Tool~ tab
page.datamine.reload: Time to reload with empty magazine:

page.datamine.reloadDualMag: Time to switch between dual mags:
page.datamine.rightbias.info: Origin refers to the point that the gun was aiming at prior to firing.
Some guns have a bias to the right (or, more rarely, to the left, which is shown with a negative value).

When a gun has a right bias, that means that, after the recoil ring is created with horizontal recoil, and offset vertically by vertical recoil, the resulting plane is rotated about the origin point by some value, approximately 50 times the data value in degrees.
For an easy visualization, see the recoil simulator in the ~Weapon Tool~ tab
page.datamine.title: Enlisted Datamine
page.soldierStats.footer: Numbers in parentheses mean the net return in bronze orders if soldier is first upgraded to 5 stars, then sold.
Values for stars of a silver order~s result are experimental and may not be completely accurate.
page.soldierStats.header: This page contains the data of the optimal rolls for soldiers based on class and rank.
Actual soldiers may have between 0 and 2 points less in each category by random chance.
page.soldierStats.soldierDamageBody: Hover over each body part to see its damage multiplier.
Note: Soviet body armor reduces damage to the mid-torso by 10%.
Helmets reduce damage to the full head by 10%,
but around half of helmets randomly don~t offer protection.
